                    </div>
                    <span>If you're any kind of a marketing geek, this is a book you have to read. Spoelstra's stories from the trenches are great fun. His success stories also make great models to work by. Granted, as one reviewer put it, these examples are fine if you have deep pockets. But don't discount them as only for big-bucks companies. A creative thinker will frequently find a way to scale down the model to fit his own paradigm. Nobody's as pragamatic as I am when it comes to marketing that makes sense for small companies. Those companies are my bread and butter. And while you might not be trying to sell Portland Trailblazers tickets to an apathetic market, there is something to be learned from their basketball-playing sumo wrestlers. </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Great for the Maverick</div>
